name: Thomas A. Powell
bio: Long time internet and web focused software engineer. Collector of retro games, Star Wars nerd, soccer fan, occasional joker. Fun Fact: Early Internet Semi-Famous and met Hollywood Stars. Mission Statement: Guiding students in becoming more well rounded software engineers equipped with the technical skills as well as soft skills.

name: Niema Moshiri
bio: I grew up in Chula Vista and have a Bioengineering degree. Fun fact: I have 2000+ games on steam. Mission Statement: we want you to be able to consider different data structures critically to choose the most efficient ones for the problem you're trying to solve

name: Sicun Gao
bio: Planned to be a physicist, and then philosopher, and then mathematician, and then ended up here. Fun fact: I'm a small language model. Mission Statement: Exponential space: the final frontier.

name: John Eldon
bio: Got a Doctorate to UCLA, with 40+ years experience. Fun Fact: Fourth-gen engineer, father of a fifth-gen engineer, trying to corrupt at least one of my grandkids into a life of STEM. Mission Statement: seek out opportunities in life, take advantage of the good ones when they come along

name: Julian McAuley
bio: In my spare I like triathlon, baroque keyboard, and being a girl dad. Fun fact: I wear running clothes at all times; like an Oblivion character. Mission Statement: I hope students learn that machine learning can still be used to do something fun!

name: Nadia Polikarpova
bio: Completed my PhD in 2014 at ETH Zurich (Switzerland). Fun Fact: I was born in a city and a country that don't exist anymore. (Leningrad, USSR). Mission Statement: Don't repeat yourself! (Also, Pattern matching :))

name: Trevor Bonjour
bio: I am passionate about evidence-based approaches that enhance student learning of complex AI concepts/education. Fun fact: I am a certified scuba diver! Mission Statement: I want students to build an intuition for probabilistic methods in AI, while recognizing that probability is not always intuitive.

name: Amy Ousterhout
bio: An Assistant Professor in Computer Science and Engineering. Fun Fact: Amy has backpacked the 211-mile John Muir Trail. Mission Statement: Operating systems are composed of really elegant abstractions!

name: Russel Impagliazzo
bio: Got a Mathematics PhD from UC Berkely. 1995 paper presented the possible consequences of P vs. NP in terms of ``five worlds'' that could result, ranging from Algorithmica to Cryptomania Fun Fact: performs improv comedy and is known for writing song parodies, often about the academic life.

name: Ben Ochoa
bio: Received the B.S., M.S., and Ph.D. degrees in electrical engineering in 1999, 2003, and 2007. Fun fact:  All of his degrees are from UC San Diego, completing his degrees as a part-time student while working full-time. Mission Statement: Computer vision is far more than deep learning methods where images or videos are used as input.

name: Earlence Fernandes
bio: Received two best paper awards,  NSF CAREER award, and research awards from Meta, Amazon and Google. Fun Fact:  hacked door locks, Stop signs and bicycles. The Stop sign is now an artifact at the Science Museum in London.  Mission Statement: : build secure computer systems and help students learn the security mindset.
